<|> 𝐏𝐲𝐭𝐡𝐨𝐧 𝐟𝐮𝐧𝐝𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐥𝐬  <|>

     >> Python 2 --> Python version 2 release in 2000.   It used to print the statement by print function.
                     for exmple --
                 print "Hello World"   ,,This code is print in python v.2.

     >> Python 3 -->Python version 3 release in 2008.  It used to print the statement by print() function.
                     for exmple --
                 print ("Hello World")   ,,This code is print in python v.3.


<|> 𝙄𝙣𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙖𝙘𝙩𝙞𝙫𝙚 𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙎𝙘𝙧𝙞𝙥𝙩 𝙢𝙤𝙙𝙚 ::--

     <::> 𝙄𝙣𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙖𝙘𝙩𝙞𝙫𝙚 𝙢𝙤𝙙𝙚 -->> 
           You can directly type python code into the python interpreter, the interpreter executes each line as you enter it,
           providing the output immediately. It is suitable for writing very short programs.
          
             for exmple --
                <> a = 2
                   b = 6
                   c = a ** b
                   print(c)  #output - 64

                <> print("Good Morning")
                            #output - Good Morning
 
                <> print(8 + 10)
                            #output - 18
      
         :: Points to view - 
                    > It gives instant result of code.
                    > You can easily test & debug lines of code.
                    > It is not suitable for long programs
                    > No code resuablity.

     <::> 𝙎𝙘𝙧𝙞𝙥𝙩 𝙢𝙤𝙙𝙚 -->> 
                 You need to write your python code in a text file and save it with the .py extension. This file called script, 
                 saved and executed using python interpreter.

           :: Points to view -
                    > Scripts allow to organise and manage the codes.
                    > It allow code resuablity.
                    > It allow to run larger and extensive programs.
                    > Late result of code because it debug entire codes.


